title: Lee appointee Christensen fights to keep District 3 seat
text:
Photo: Liz Hafalia, The Chronicle SF supervisor Julie Christensen with director Rita Mah of the Chinese Newcomers Service Cente visit storeowners in Chinatown in San Francisco, Calif., on Tuesday, October 6, 2015. Trashcans will be placed in front of merchants' stores to increase pedestrian access to trash receptacles and decrease illegal dumping as part of the Keep Chinatown Clean program. SF supervisor Julie Christensen with director Rita Mah of the...
On paper, Julie Christensen’s resume makes her look like a settled-in city dweller trying to make life for her neighbors a little better. She has fought for libraries and pools and even helped design the KitchenAid candy-apple-red mixer. Little about her seems threatening.
